{
  "texts": [
    "For many of the datasets and applications relevant to AI polling, we see opinion surveys of various sizes being augmented with external data, either by aggregating multiple surveys together, as described by Warshaw, or by linking surveys with separate Big Data, such as VR files.",
    "To describe this 'intermezzo' of the data space, neither entirely 'Big' nor entirely 'Small', Callegaro and Yang (2018) coin the term 'Small Big Data'.",
    "We have now introduced a significant innovation in the polling industry.",
    "We call it 'artificially intelligent polling', as it is underpinned by narrow AI.",
    "It is typically fuelled by 'Small Big Data'."
  ]
}